<h1> Napowrimo 2020 day 9 - Hollow Passengers </h1>
<p><i>Published on: <time datetime="2024-07-16T11:05:30.161Z">July 16, 2024</time></i></p>
    
       <a href="/posts/tag/posts">#posts</a>
    
       <a href="/posts/tag/poetry">#poetry</a>
    
</br>
<p>The destination displays are corrupted<br>
again. Carriages and corridors converge<br>
on the horizon, a lifetime's walk away.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>If you look to your left, you will<br>
see the same wheat field repeated<br>
endlessly, the blur devoid of detail.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Our mobile phones died decades ago. Good<br>
books were bartered for the smallest<br>
pleasures, perhaps a window seat, maybe<br>
an air vent that isn't clogged with dust.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We have a selection of sandwiches<br>
available in the buffet car; egg,<br>
ploughman's or gravel (no mayo).</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Those who wander too far from their seats<br>
are quickly forgotten. They become memories<br>
then stories, then names, then silences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We regret to inform you the past<br>
is a black hole and it is hungry.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Mostly, we sit very still and listen to<br>
our toenails grow, millimetre by millimetre.</p>
<hr>
<p>Prompt became the title - &quot;Hollow Passengers&quot; from <a href="https://www.instagram.com/lemondaisypoetry/">Lemondaisypoetry</a> on Instagram</p>

